1. Update system
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

2. Install Java (MANDATORY)

Nexus requires Java 8 or 11. Use Java 11.

sudo apt install openjdk-11-jdk -y


Verify:

java -version


If Java isn’t installed correctly, stop here. Nexus won’t run.

3. Create Nexus user (DO NOT RUN AS ROOT)
sudo adduser nexus

4. Download Nexus
cd /opt
sudo wget https://download.sonatype.com/nexus/3/nexus-3-latest-unix.tar.gz

5. Extract Nexus
sudo tar -xvf nexus-3-latest-unix.tar.gz


Rename for simplicity:

sudo mv nexus-3* nexus


Create data directory:

sudo mkdir sonatype-work

6. Set ownership
sudo chown -R nexus:nexus /opt/nexus
sudo chown -R nexus:nexus /opt/sonatype-work

7. Configure Nexus to run as nexus user

Edit file:

sudo nano /opt/nexus/bin/nexus.rc


Add / change:

run_as_user="nexus"


Save and exit.

8. Create systemd service
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/nexus.service


Paste exactly this:

[Unit]
Description=Nexus Repository Manager
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=forking
LimitNOFILE=65536
ExecStart=/opt/nexus/bin/nexus start
ExecStop=/opt/nexus/bin/nexus stop
User=nexus
Restart=on-abort

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target


Save.

9. Reload & start Nexus
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable nexus
sudo systemctl start nexus


Check status:

sudo systemctl status nexus


If it’s not ACTIVE, don’t proceed. Fix errors first.

10. Open firewall (if enabled)
sudo ufw allow 8081

11. Access Nexus

Open browser:

http://<SERVER-IP>:8081


Example:

http://54.xx.xx.xx:8081

12. Get admin password
cat /opt/sonatype-work/nexus3/admin.password


Login:

Username: admin

Password: from above command
